Hello! I've got two forms (one after another) in my template (and I need both). So it looks something like this:
```            &lt;script&gt;
                hbspt.forms.create({
                    portalId: "XXXXX",
                    formId: "F1",
                    onFormReady: function($form) {
            F1X1();
                    },
                    onFormSubmit: function($form) { 
            F1X2();
                    }
                });
            &lt;/script&gt;
            &lt;script&gt;
                hbspt.forms.create({
                    portalId: "XXXXX",
                    formId: "F2",
                    onFormReady: function($form) {
			F2X1();
                    },
                    onFormSubmit: function($form) { 
			F2X2();
                    }
                });
            &lt;/script&gt;```
For some reason, F2X2() so, and **onFormSubmit** in general, for the second form doesn't get executed. Any idea why, or rather, how to fix it?
PS. *F2X1()* for *onFormReady* works fine, only **onFormSubmit** doesn't.
